Senator Dino Melaye, who was reported kidnapped yesterday has apparently resurfaced. In a post on his twitter handle, Melaye wrote; “I thank God once again for escaping another dangerous attack. I also thank Nigerians for their prayers and show of Love. Spent 11 hours in the wilderness traumatized but God preserved me. God is the best and in whom ONLY I trust. They will continue to try. WE SHALL OVERCOME!!!” Melaye who is Chairman, Senate Committee on Federal Capital Territory, was reportedly kidnapped by unknown gunmen on his way to Kogi from Abuja for a scheduled court appearance. His alleged kidnap came less than forty-eight hours after his defection from the All Progressives Congress (APC) to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Ben Murray-Bruce, who chairs the Senate Committee on Privatization confirmed the lawmaker’s abduction on his Twitter handle on Thursday. He disclosed that Melaye’s brother made the revelation to him as he was on his way from Abuja to his home state, Kogi. “I have just been informed by Moses Melaye, @dino_melaye’s brother, that Dino has been abducted by unknown persons in a Toyota Sienna that blocked their car and overpowered them on their way to Kogi to answer to Dino’s court case. Lets be on the watch out. Will keep you updated,” he tweeted via his Twitter handle @benmurraybruce. The police yesterday, announced that they have begun an investigation into the the alleged kidnap of the senator. 